# Production secrets — NEVER in git

The `production/` folder and VPS deploy scripts are **local/server only**.

## MUST NOT reach GitHub

- `production/env/api.env`, `web.env.production`, `admin.env`, `docker.env`, `vps.env`
- `production/deploy-to-vps.sh`, `sync-models-to-vps.sh`, `switch-to-domain.sh`, `README.md`, `DNS-CUTOVER.md`
- `production/vps.env.example`, `vps.env.domain.example` (may contain your real host/IP)
- `production/ssh/id_*`, `*.pem`
- `infra/pm2.ecosystem.config.js` (real server paths)
- `infra/scripts/vps-*.sh`, `sync-to-vps.sh`, `repair-api-port.sh`, `bootstrap-vps.sh`, `first-deploy.sh`, `install-nginx-ip.sh`, `install-nginx-domain.sh`
- Any file with real VPS IP, domain, phone, passwords, tokens, or connection strings

## Allowed in git

- `production/env/README.md`
- `production/env/*.example` (placeholders only — no real hosts)
- `production/ssh/README.md`
- `infra/pm2.ecosystem.config.example.js` (generic template)
- Generic infra: `deploy.sh`, `migrate.sh`, `docker-compose.prod.yml`, `nginx.conf` (no real IP)

## Agent protocol

1. **NEVER** `git add` paths under `production/` except `env/*.example`, `env/README.md`, `ssh/README.md`.
2. **NEVER** `git add` VPS deploy scripts listed above.
3. **NEVER** paste real production values into committed files, PRs, or chat logs when avoidable.
4. Use placeholders (`YOUR_VPS_IP`, `yourdomain.com`) in docs committed to GitHub.
5. If the user asks to commit production/VPS files, **refuse** and point to `production/env/README.md`.
